          "question": "What is Guacamole?",
          "answer": "Apache Guacamole is a clientless remote desktop gateway that supports standard protocols like VNC, RDP, and SSH. Contact a Platform Administrator for more information about deploying Guacamole for your Project."
        },
        {
          "question": "What is JupyterHub?",
          "answer": "JupyterHub is an open-source, multi-user version of Jupyter Notebook integrated for performing analysis of data in the VRE Core. Contact a Platform Administrator for more information about deploying JupyterHub for your Project."
        },
        {
          "question": "What is Superset?",
          "answer": "Apache Superset is an open-source software cloud-native application designed for the exploration and visualization of big data. Contact a Platform Administrator for more information about deploying Superset for your Project."
        },
        {
          "question": "What is the Command Line Tool?",
          "answer": "The Command Line Tool supports file upload, folder upload, Project query, and File Manifest functions from a Linux or Mac Command Line."
        }
